 GCC 10 Lambda Capture/Parameter Conflict Fix
 ============================================

 GCC 10 enforces stricter C++ rules where a lambda cannot have both a
 capture and a parameter with the same name 'CGF'.

 There are exactly 3 instances in CGOpenMPRuntime.cpp (LLVM 3.9.1) where
 lambdas capture '&CGF' AND have 'CodeGenFunction &CGF' as a parameter.

 Apply with sed (recommended):
 -----------------------------

 cd tools/clang/lib/CodeGen

 # Fix line ~6076: BeginThenGen lambda
 sed -i 's/\[&D, &CGF, &BasePointersArray/[&D, &BasePointersArray/g' CGOpenMPRuntime.cpp

 # Fix line ~6124: EndThenGen lambda
 sed -i 's/\[&CGF, &BasePointersArray/[&BasePointersArray/g' CGOpenMPRuntime.cpp

 # Fix line ~6191: ThenGen lambda
 sed -i 's/\[&D, &CGF, Device\]/[&D, Device]/g' CGOpenMPRuntime.cpp

 Manual fixes:
 -------------

 Line ~6076:
 BEFORE: auto &&BeginThenGen = [&D, &CGF, &BasePointersArray, &PointersArray,
 AFTER:  auto &&BeginThenGen = [&D, &BasePointersArray, &PointersArray,

 Line ~6124:
 BEFORE: auto &&EndThenGen = [&CGF, &BasePointersArray, &PointersArray, &SizesArray,
 AFTER:  auto &&EndThenGen = [&BasePointersArray, &PointersArray, &SizesArray,

 Line ~6191:
 BEFORE: auto &&ThenGen = [&D, &CGF, Device](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {
 AFTER:  auto &&ThenGen = [&D, Device](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {

 The CGF reference in the lambda body will use the parameter, not the capture.
